docs.abstract: The move by the group of young climate activists was another sign that left-wing advocacy organizations have increasingly coalesced around the Vermont senator’s candidacy.
docs.snippet: The move by the group of young climate activists was another sign that left-wing advocacy organizations have increasingly coalesced around the Vermont senator’s candidacy.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Sunrise Movement, the collection of young climate activists who have roiled Capitol Hill and the Democratic presidential primary,  announced on Thursday that it was endorsing Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, in another sign that left-wing advocacy groups have increasingly coalesced around his candidacy.

headline.main: Bernie Sanders’s Latest Endorsement: Sunrise Movement
headline.print_headline: Sanders Gets Endorsement Of Young Climate Group, Bolstering Left-Wing Ties

docs.abstract: We sat down with Democratic presidential candidates and asked them a new set of questions, including how they’d debate President Trump to the last book they read.
docs.snippet: We sat down with Democratic presidential candidates and asked them a new set of questions, including how they’d debate President Trump to the last book they read.
docs.lead_paragraph: The first time we interviewed the Democratic presidential candidates, late last spring, we had a pile of yes-or-no, either-or policy questions to ask, many of them representing litmus-test issues at the heart of Democratic politics: single-payer health care and foreign wars, wealth concentration and tech regulation.

docs.lead_paragraph: Joshua Kucera knows a lot about the Caucasus. He’s a freelance journalist living in Georgia (the country, not the state), and covers the region for various media outlets.

docs.abstract: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
docs.snippet: Making a case for the nomination, onstage together for one last time in 2019.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Elizabeth Warren argued that Democrats would defeat President Trump if they “draw the sharpest distinction” with what she called the administration’s corruption — and suggested that Mayor Pete Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raising would undermine their ability to do that. Mr. Buttigieg said his party could scarcely afford to hew to such “purity tests” in a race against Mr. Trump.

headline.main: Who’s Best to Beat Trump? 7 Answers When 7 Democrats Debate
headline.print_headline: Who Is the Most Electable of Them All?

docs.abstract: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
docs.snippet: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One day after seven candidates took the stage for the most intimate debate of the Democratic presidential primary cycle so far, the Democratic National Committee increased the qualification standards for its next debate in January, making it likely that the field of candidates will be winnowed even further for the event.

headline.main: January Debate Will Be Harder to Qualify For, D.N.C. Announces
headline.print_headline: Stricter Standards In the Next Round
